Hi,

As a maintainer of Gthumb Debian package I did a patch following
the suggestion of "directly assigning the buffer to NULL after the first call of g_free(buffer)."

I did an upload to unstable at the beginning of the week and I just
did an upload to security-master.

If the upstream do something different than that I update the patch.

edited:
```
--- gthumb-3.3.1.orig/extensions/contact_sheet/dlg-contact-sheet.c
+++ gthumb-3.3.1/extensions/contact_sheet/dlg-contact-sheet.c
@@ -352,6 +352,7 @@ add_themes_from_dir (DialogData *data,
                if (! g_key_file_load_from_data (key_file, buffer, size, G_KEY_FILE_NONE, NULL)) {
                        g_key_file_free (key_file);
                        g_free (buffer);
+                       buffer = NULL;
                        g_object_unref (file);
                        g_object_unref (file_info);
                }
```














Regards,
Herbert

